comment: * @hide Only a subset of ICU is exposed in Android

variables.name: SEC_COMMON_LOW
variables.comment: Secondary level: Compress up to 33 common weights as 05..25 or 25..45.

variables.name: CASE_LOWER_FIRST_COMMON_LOW
variables.comment: Case level, lowerFirst: Compress up to 7 common weights as 1..7 or 7..13.

variables.name: CASE_UPPER_FIRST_COMMON_LOW
variables.comment: Case level, upperFirst: Compress up to 13 common weights as 3..15.

variables.name: TER_ONLY_COMMON_LOW
variables.comment: Tertiary level only (no case): Compress up to 97 common weights as 05..65 or 65..C5.

variables.name: TER_LOWER_FIRST_COMMON_LOW
variables.comment: Tertiary with case, lowerFirst: Compress up to 33 common weights as 05..25 or 25..45.

variables.name: TER_UPPER_FIRST_COMMON_LOW
variables.comment: Tertiary with case, upperFirst: Compress up to 33 common weights as 85..A5 or A5..C5.

variables.name: QUAT_COMMON_LOW
variables.comment: Quaternary level: Compress up to 113 common weights as 1C..8C or 8C..FC.

variables.name: levelMasks
variables.comment:
* Map from collation strength (UColAttributeValue) to a mask of Collation.Level bits up to that
     * strength, excluding the CASE_LEVEL which is independent of the strength, and excluding
     * IDENTICAL_LEVEL which this function does not write.

methods.name: private static SortKeyLevel getSortKeyLevel(int levels, int level)

public static void writeSortKeyUpToQuaternary(CollationIterator iter, boolean[] compressibleBytes, CollationSettings settings, SortKeyByteSink sink, int minLevel, LevelCallback callback, boolean preflight)
methods.comment:
* Writes the sort key bytes for minLevel up to the iterator data's strength. Optionally writes
     * the case level. Stops writing levels when callback.needToWrite(level) returns false.
     * Separates levels with the LEVEL_SEPARATOR_BYTE but does not write a TERMINATOR_BYTE.
